article.headline: Virginia 80, Hampton 54
article.story: CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. -- Sylven Landesberg scored 14 points, grabbed a career-high 12 rebounds and dished out six assists to lead Virginia over Hampton 80-54 on Wednesday night. Virginia (6-4) made a season-high 11 3-pointers and outrebounded Hampton 41-26. Sammy Zeglinski added 13 points as the Cavaliers won their second straight. The Pirates (2-10) were led by Kwame Morgan?s 18 points. Virginia jumped out to a 12-0 lead in the first six minutes, while Hampton committed six turnovers. Two 3-pointers by Morgan helped Hampton closed the gap to 15-8, but Virginia responded with a 25-10 onslaught, including 3-pointers by Zeglinski, Jeff Jones, Will Sherrill and Mustapha Farrakhan, to lead 40-18. The Cavaliers, who shot 56 percent in the half, led 48-28 at the break. Virginia played its third game in a row without starting power forward Mike Scott, who has a sprained right ankle.
